               <history>
                  <provenance>This manuscript had originally been kept at <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0302SanStefano">Santo Stefano de' Mori</placeName>, see
                     <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/QSJFS6EP"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Rahlfs1917Textausgaben"/><title level="m">Nissel und Petraeus, ihre äthiopischen Textausgaben und Typen</title><title level="s">Nachrichten von der K. Gesellschaft der Wissenschaft zu Göttingen. Philologisch-historische Klasse</title><author><forename>Alfred</forename><surname>Rahlfs</surname></author><pubPlace>Göttingen</pubPlace><date>1917</date><series><title level="s">Nachrichten von der K. Gesellschaft der Wissenschaft zu Göttingen. Philologisch-historische Klasse</title></series><note type="url">https://www.deutsche-digitale-bibliothek.de/item/LM567XXM5LEAJGYTN4EGPH3KT6MH5U4D</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Rahlfs1917Textausgaben</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Rahlfs1917Textausgaben</note><citedRange unit="page">283</citedRange></bibl>.
                     According to Dillmann, this manuscript belonged to <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11545Laurence">Richard Laurence</persName>, see     <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NMHJ56PR"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1848Catalogus"/><title level="m">Catalogus codicum manuscriptorum Bibliothecae Bodleianae Oxoniensis, Pars VII: Codices Aethiopici</title><author><forename>Christian Friedrich August</forename><surname>Dillmann</surname></author><pubPlace>Oxonii</pubPlace><publisher>E Typographeo Academico</publisher><date>1848</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/CatalogiCodicumManuscriptorumBibliothP7</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Oxford</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">bm:Dillmann1848Catalogus</note></note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Oxford</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">bm:Dillmann1848Catalogus</note><citedRange unit="page">10a</citedRange></bibl>. According to Brock, the manuscript was, together with <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BDLaethd13">Oxford, Bodleian Library, Bodleian Aeth. d. 13</ref>,
                     amongst those purchased by the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0312BDL">Bodleian Library</placeName> in <date when="1693"/> from Robert Huntington,
                     see
                     <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/RDZF3CLU"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Gnisci2019Treasures"/><title level="m">Treasures of Ethiopia and Eritrea in the Bodleian Library, Oxford</title><title level="s">Manar al-Athar Monograph</title><editor><forename>Jacopo</forename><surname>Gnisci</surname></editor><pubPlace>Oxford</pubPlace><publisher>Manar Al-Athar</publisher><date>2019</date><series><title level="s">Manar al-Athar Monograph</title><biblScope unit="volume">5</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">5</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Gnisci2019Treasures</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Gnisci2019Treasures</note><citedRange unit="page">3</citedRange></bibl>. Given both Laurence's remarks on his acquisition of 
                     <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BDLaethd13">Oxford, Bodleian Library, Bodleian Aeth. d. 13</ref> in     <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/IJSUVIA5"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Laurence1819Ascensio"/><title level="m">Ascensio Isaiae vatis</title><author><forename>Richard</forename><surname>Laurence</surname></author><pubPlace>Oxoniae</pubPlace><publisher>Typis Academicis</publisher><date>1819</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/ascensioisaiaeva00laur</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Laurence1819Ascensio</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Laurence1819Ascensio</note><citedRange unit="page">v</citedRange></bibl>
                     and the lack of mentions of these
                     manuscripts in records reported
                     by Brock, this seems unlikely.</provenance>
               </history>
               
